&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/golfforbeginners/~4/inqS92qVLSE" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><app:edited xmlns:app="http://www.w3.org/2007/app">2012-02-14T10:58:44.910-05:00</app:edited><thr:total xmlns:thr="http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0">3</thr:total><feedburner:origLink>http://golf-for-beginners.blogspot.com/2012/02/phil-mickelson-mentally-superior-to.html</feedburner:origLink></item><item><title>Tiger Woods ready to win at least three golf tournaments in 2012?</title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/golfforbeginners/~3/RJq6eh_Bg0Q/tiger-woods-ready-to-win-at-least-three.html</link><category>Chevron World Challenge</category><category>ATT Pebble Beach</category><category>golf tournaments</category><category>Tiger Woods</category><category>Steve Siebold</category><author>golfforbeginners@aol.com (Stacy and Barry Solomon)</author><pubDate>Fri, 10 Feb 2012 08:31:53 PST</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-10712965.post-9218889193549099239</guid><description>&lt;div class='posterous_autopost'&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.pgatour.com/2012/tournaments/r005/02/09/tiger-round1/index.html" title="Tiger Woods opener strong but irons need work" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: blue;"&gt;Tiger Woods&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; kicks off his 2012 PGA Tour season this week at The AT&amp;amp;T Pebble Beach National Pro-Am. Woods has been working hard on a new swing with coach Sean Foley and his mental game is also looking sharp, leading one expert to predict that Tiger will win at least three times on tour this year. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&lt;div class='p_embed p_image_embed'&gt; &lt;img alt="Tiger-woods_pebble_beach" height="253" src="http://getfile6.posterous.com/getfile/files.posterous.com/temp-2012-02-10/wgtAkgdsgDCDtkofrIbiDkFJanpbEAliqIvAIwEaDhebwppqgbzluklFiyJg/Tiger-Woods_Pebble_Beach.jpg.scaled500.jpg" width="380" /&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: xx-small;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.csmonitor.com/USA/Latest-News-Wires/2012/0210/Tiger-Woods-returns-to-form-at-Pebble-Beach" title="Tiger Woods" target="_blank"&gt;Tiger Woods&lt;/a&gt;, SpyGlass Hill Golf Course, Round One&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Steve Siebold, a former professional athlete (tennis player), mental toughness coach and author of the book &lt;em&gt;177 &lt;a href="http://mentaltoughnessu.com/steve_siebold.htm" title="Mental Toughness" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: blue;"&gt;Mental Toughness &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Secrets of The World Class&lt;/em&gt;, has worked with athletes for&amp;nbsp;twenty-seven years and has been pointing to a Tiger Woods comeback all along, but based on what&amp;rsquo;s he&amp;rsquo;s seeing now he believes this is the year of the Tiger. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s why:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot; &lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://golf-for-beginners.blogspot.com/2012/01/will-tiger-woods-golf-season-debut-be.html" title="Will Tiger Woods golf season debut be a hit or a Miss? " target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: blue;"&gt;Tiger Woods' &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;talent never left him; it was his confidence that disappeared. Now that he knows how to win again, he&amp;rsquo;s not going to stop. Tiger won his last PGA Tour start, The &lt;a href="http://golf-for-beginners.blogspot.com/2011/12/does-it-matter-how-many-golfers-tiger.html" title="Does it matter how many golfers Tiger Woods had to beat at Chevron?" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span style="color: blue;"&gt;Chevron World Challenge&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; on December 4th and finished third at the Abu Dhabi HSBC Golf Championship. His confidence is as high as it&amp;rsquo;s been in years.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;In his first round of the ATT at Spyglass Hill Golf course, Woods fired off six birdies for an opening round of 68, hitting eleven of fourteen fairways and fifteen of eighteen greens in regulation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot; &lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;His ball control is much better than it&amp;rsquo;s been, and he&amp;rsquo;s working the ball left to right and right to left comfortably. Both physically and mentally he looks really healthy and his competition should be scared. He&amp;rsquo;s going to win at least three times this season.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot; &lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://golf-for-beginners.blogspot.com/2012/01/golf-courses-that-inspire-unfolding.html" title="Golf courses that inspire and unfolding drama" target="_blank"&gt;Pebble Beach &lt;/a&gt;will be a good start for Tiger. He won the 2000 U.S. Open at Pebble Beach by&amp;nbsp;fifteen shots. He knows how to win big on this track. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Woods has made adversity his mental training ground. The stress and struggles of the past few years have only made him that much tougher and he&amp;rsquo;s ready to dominate the game again.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Woods is hard-wired through years of world-class programming to focus on a vision and persevere at any cost. He doesn&amp;rsquo;t understand what giving up is.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;middot; &lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=""&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Champions like Woods are professional failures. They know that success is based on a series of comebacks, and that setbacks are set-ups for comebacks. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The bottom line for Siebold?&lt;/em&gt; A bet against a champion like Tiger Woods is a bad bet. On the physical plane he has perseverance, on the mental plane he has toughness and on the spiritual plane he has artistry...so says Siebold.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial,sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"&gt;I agree with Steve Siebold that a bet against Woods at this point in his resurgence is a strong one but it should also be weighed heavily against other golfers in the field. In this stage of his career, with negatives drifting behind him, I think that Woods has the potential to win several golf tournaments this season, including a major &lt;em&gt;(U.S. Open perhaps? He won it before hobbling on one leg...)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"&gt;Voice your opinion on Twitter &lt;a href="http://www.twitter.com/golf4beginners" title="Golf4Beginners on Twitter" target="_blank"&gt;@Golf4Beginners &lt;/a&gt;and friend on &lt;a href="http://www.facebook.com/golfforbeginners" title="Golf for Beginners on Facebook" target="_blank"&gt;Facebook&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p style="line-height: normal; margin-bottom: 0pt;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style="font-size: 10px;"&gt; &lt;a href="http://posterous.com"&gt;Posted via email&lt;/a&gt;  from &lt;a href="http://stacysolomon.posterous.com/why-tiger-woods-should-win-at-least-three-gol"&gt;stacysolomon's posterous&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;Follow Golf4Beginners on Twitter!&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/10712965-9218889193549099239?l=golf-for-beginners.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
